ownedComment.body: An amount of a quantity type that is the value of an individual property of some thing or things. A quantity may be denoted by a quantity value, or by a definite description, e.g., the mass of one centilitre of water at standard temperature and pressure. This is one definition of 'quantity' as used in the VIM. This model makes quantity an object-type, a thing in its own right, which can be the value of multiple distinct properties of different objects. ts.
The abstract domain of a quantity, the generic kind of thing taken on by a measurable property -- time, length, mass, etc. This is one definition of 'quantity' in the VIM.

A specific quantity of a given quantity type that is defined by a system of units to be a base for expressing quantity values that represent quantities of that quantity type. A measurement unit may or may not have a name. Some measurement units only have a symbol.

ownedComment.body: The concept type stereotype identifies a UML class as an SBVR 'concept type', that is, a classifier whose instances are classes.

The categorization type stereotype characterizes a class as a SBVR 'categorization type;, a classifier whose instances are a set of mutually exclusive subtypes of a common base concept (class). Each categorization type has a 'categorization' dependency on a 'base class' that is the "common base concept" of the instances..

the verb concept role stereotype characterizes a UML association as a representation of a SBVR 'verb concept role'. The association that is the verb concept role has the same name as the association end and is the placeholder for the verb concept role in the verb concept Each verb concept role association represents exactly one verb concept role in exactly one SBVR verb concept. In a verb concept role association only the association end that refers to the range of the role is navigable, and it always has multiplicity one, because each verb concept role is played exactly once in an actuality of the verb concept.cept.

the verb concept stereotype characterizes a nominal UML class as a SBVR 'verb concept'. Each verb concept has a set of verb concept roles, each of which characterizes the behavior of one participant in the state or event conceptualized by the verb concept. Each verb concept has an 'arity', which is the fixed number of roles played in each instance of the verb concept.t.
